data.description: Nestled at the end of a private cul-de-sac in the coveted Loch Highland lake community, this home is the epitome of elegance and comfort. The kitchen, a modern chef's dream, includes gleaming granite countertops and stainless steel appliances, and recessed lighting. Experience tranquility on the serene screened porch, or the private rear deck, both being perfect for morning coffees or evening relaxation.    The family room, crowned with a soaring cathedral ceiling with exposed beams, is anchored by a majestic floor-to-ceiling stone fireplace, creating a warm and inviting ambiance. Beautiful hardwood floors add to the charm throughout the main level, adding a touch of sophistication. The upper level guest bathroom has been tastefully updated, and the main level offers a versatile bedroom or office space complemented by a full bath—ideal for an in-law suite or guest quarters. The primary bedroom is large with exposed beam, large closets, and a retro ensuite bathroom. Fresh paint and contemporary lighting fixtures add the finishing touches to this exquisite home.    The finished terrace level is an active persons delight, featuring a spacious recreation room for movies, exercise, and a chic 70's style wet bar. For the hobbyists and DIY enthusiasts, a separate workshop awaits, complete with a garage door, workbenches, overhead lighting, and both 117/240v power.     Here in Loch Highland, residents relish an array of amenities: an active HOA, two sparkling pools with a swim team, a picturesque lake equipped not just beautiful views, but one with a fishing pier and boat ramp, four tennis courts, and a playground for the little ones. Despite its Roswell address, this gem benefits from desirable Cobb County schools as the property resides in the highly respected and sought after East Cobb school district which includes Garrison Mill Elementary, Mabry Middle, and Lassiter High School. Another benefit is the property tax rates, which is beneficial to seniors.     Location is key, and this home doesn't disappoint. Situated just minutes from Hwy. 92, you're at the doorstep of premier shopping, diverse dining, vibrant entertainment venues, and some of the area's top parks and recreational spots. Don't miss the chance to call this sanctuary 'home'. ***Currently, this house has a VA Mortgage that is assumable (to a Veteran or even a non-Veteran) with a 2.25% interest on the balance of approx. $303k. That is an attractive financing option, but you'd need to make up the difference between the balance of this loan and contracted sales price with EITHER in cash OR another 2nd mortgage.***
